chucho valdes & the afro cuban messengers events at stanford chucho valdes & the afro cuban messengers facebook twitter email print add to calendar to experience jesus chucho valdes in concert is to enjoy an audience with a whirlwind as some of the most virtuosic piano playing in jazz history meets an ever surprising array of rhythms tempi and global influences afro cuban hard bop european classical and more the founder of the legendary cuban jazz ensemble irakere valdes won a 2011 grammy for his cd with his new afro cuban messengers chucho's steps which all about jazz called a force of nature whose vigor bursts out of the speakers and sweeps everything away before it generously supported by fred and stephanie harman and by kcsm jazz 91 part of the koret jazz project when sunday february 19 2012 7 00 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags arts performance music sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission reserved seating $38 42 permalink http events stanford edu events 284 28497 more info last modified february 2 2012
